nvidia-graphics-drivers-364 (364.15-0ubuntu1~gpu16.04.1) xenial; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release

 -- Michael Marley <michael@michaelmarley.com>  Wed, 06 Apr 2016 16:15:00 -0400

nvidia-graphics-drivers-364 (364.12-0ubuntu1~gpu16.04.2) xenial; urgency=medium

  * debian/71-nvidia.rules, debian/rules, debian/framebuffer-nvidia,
    debian/templates/nvidia-graphics-drivers.install.in:
    - Keep KMS disabled, as it prevents hybrid graphics and SLI from
      working. To enable KMS, users can set modeset=1 (instead of 0) in
      /etc/modprobe.d/nvidia-graphics-drivers.conf, and update the
      initramfs.
    - Add an initramfs hook for users who run encrypted systems.
    - Correct the module aliases, so that modprobe works correctly.

 -- Alberto Milone <alberto.milone@canonical.com>  Fri, 25 Mar 2016 16:31:28 +0100

nvidia-graphics-drivers-364 (364.12-0ubuntu1~gpu16.04.1) xenial; urgency=medium

  * New upstream release.
  * debian/templates/control.in:
    - Drop transitional packages.
    - Add build dependency on libwayland-dev.
  * debian/templates/nvidia-graphics-drivers.dirs.in,
    debian/templates/nvidia-graphics-drivers.install.in:
    - Install nvidia-drm-outputclass.conf.
    - Add support for Vulkan.
  * debian/71-nvidia.rules, debian/templates/dkms.conf.fragment.in,
    debian/templates/dkms_nvidia.conf.in:
    - Build the nvidia-drm module.
    - Load the nvidia-drm module, and enable KMS.

